  "name": "Buccaneer's Blood (Skull and Shackles)",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/tools/navigation/map-chart-tan.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelType\">One of your ancestors was an infamous Free Captain of the Shackles, whose very name struck fear in the hearts of those who sailed the seas in search of an honest living. Piracy is in your blood, and you&rsquo;ve always longed to follow in your forebear&rsquo;s footsteps and plunder the shipping lanes.&nbsp;</span>You went to a tavern called the Formidably Maid, a notorious pirate hangout in Port Peril, eager to start your career as a buccaneer. While you were there, however, a dashing and flirtatious corsair caught your eye, and after a whirlwind night of booze and romance, you found yourself beaten senseless and stuffed in a sack, carried off to who knows where.</p></em>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelType\">You gain a +1 trait bonus on Intimidate and Profession (sailor) checks. In addition, you gain a one-time +1 trait bonus to your Disrepute and Infamy scores (see &ldquo;The Life of a Pirate&rdquo; in <em>Pathfinder Adventure Path #55 </em>for details on the Infamy system).</span></p>",
